      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 1781: `isPeerAuthorized()` accepts a device when `uriFromDevice(deviceId)` returns empty. That means any member or invited user can authorize an unknown/untracked device id as long as the issuer URI is a valid member, which defeats the device-membership portion of the authorization check. For established conversations, unknown devices should be rejected unless there is an explicit invite/bootstrap path that requires otherwise.\n```suggestion\nauto mappedUri \u003d uriFromDevice(deviceId);\nreturn !mappedUri.empty() \u0026\u0026 mappedUri \u003d\u003d uri;\n```",
      "revId": "ee2a308118da652c7139ca27cb2982aade2fe231",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
