      "writtenOn": "2026-05-20T20:23:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2268: The incoming git channel no longer verifies that the device embedded in the channel name (`git://\u003cdevice\u003e/\u003cconversation\u003e`) matches the local device being requested. This allows an authorized conversation member to open a server-side git channel using an arbitrary target device id, which weakens the channel-binding hardening this patch is trying to add. Keep parsing the requested device from `name` and reject requests not addressed to this account/device before authorizing the peer.\n```suggestion\nauto requestedDevice \u003d name.substr(6, sep - 6);\nif (requestedDevice !\u003d currentDeviceId().toString()) {\n    JAMI_WARNING(\"[Account {:s}] [Conversation {}] Git server requested for unexpected device {}\",\n                 getAccountID(),\n                 conversationId,\n                 requestedDevice);\n    channel-\u003eshutdown();\n    return;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "ee2a308118da652c7139ca27cb2982aade2fe231",
